author: Rob Goldberg
title: Bears Reportedly 'Actively' Seeking Trade Partner for Jay Cutler | Bleacher Report
text: Bears Reportedly 'Actively' Seeking Trade Partner for Jay Cutler Stacy Revere/Getty Images Featured Columnist February 21, 2017 The Chicago Bears are hoping to rebuild this offseason and that begins with the quarterback. According to ESPN's Adam Schefter , the team has "actively started seeking a trade partner" for Jay Cutler . Injuries limited the 33-year-old to just five games last season as he finished with just four touchdowns and five interceptions. His 78.1 quarterback rating was the second-worst of his career. More to follow.
